    'section2': 'II. GENERAL PRINCIPLES AND CONDITIONS FOR PROCESSING PERSONAL DATA',
    'section2A': 'A. Principles for Processing Personal Data',
    'section2AContent': 'Your personal data is processed by Smile Hair Clinic in accordance with the personal data processing principles set forth in Article 4 of KVKK and Article 5 of GDPR. Compliance with these principles is mandatory for each personal data processing activity:\n\nProcessing personal data in accordance with law and rules of integrity:\nIn the processing of your personal data, we act in accordance with laws, secondary regulations and general principles of law; we pay attention to processing personal data limited to the purpose of processing and taking into account the reasonable expectations of the Relevant Person.\n\nPersonal data being accurate and up-to-date:\nAttention is paid to whether the processed personal data is up-to-date and controls are made in this regard. The Relevant Person is granted the right to request correction or deletion of inaccurate and outdated data in this context.\n\nProcessing personal data for specific, explicit and legitimate purposes:\nBefore each personal data processing activity, data processing purposes are determined and compliance with these purposes being lawful is observed.\n\nPersonal data being connected, limited and measured with the purpose for which it is processed:\nPersonal data necessary for achieving the collection purpose is limited in data processing activities and necessary technical and administrative measures are taken to prevent processing of personal data unrelated to this purpose.\n\nRetention of personal data for the period required by the legislation or processing purposes:\nPersonal data is deleted, destroyed or anonymized after the personal data processing purpose is eliminated or the period foreseen in the legislation expires.',
    'section2B': 'B. Conditions for Processing Personal Data',
    'section2BContent': 'Your personal data is processed by Smile Hair Clinic provided that at least one of the personal data processing conditions set forth in Article 5 of KVKK and Article 6 and following of GDPR exists. Explanations regarding these conditions are provided below:\n\nExistence of Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person:\nPersonal data of the Relevant Person can be processed if the Relevant Person gives consent with free will, having sufficient information about the personal data processing activity, in a way that leaves no room for doubt and limited only to that transaction.\n\nExplicitly provided for in laws:\nPersonal data can be processed within the framework of the relevant legal regulation without the Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person if it is explicitly provided for in laws.\n\nInability to obtain Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person due to actual impossibility and necessity of personal data processing:\nPersonal data belonging to the Relevant Person who is unable to express consent or whose consent cannot be recognized as valid can be processed without seeking Explicit Consent if personal data processing is necessary to protect the life or physical integrity of the Relevant Person or a third person.\n\nPersonal data processing activity being directly related to the establishment or performance of a contract:\nPersonal data processing activity can be performed without seeking Explicit Consent if it is necessary to process personal data belonging to the parties of a contract established or already signed between the relevant person and Smile Hair Clinic.\n\nNecessity of personal data processing activity for the Data Controller to fulfill its legal obligation:\nPersonal data can be processed without seeking Explicit Consent for the purpose of fulfilling legal obligations foreseen within the scope of the legislation in force.\n\nPublic disclosure of personal data by the Relevant Person:\nPersonal data disclosed to the public by the Relevant Person in any way and which has become accessible to everyone as a result of this disclosure can be processed limited to the purpose of disclosure without the Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person.\n\nNecessity of personal data processing for establishment, exercise or protection of a right:\nPersonal data of the Relevant Person can be processed if data processing is necessary for establishment, exercise or protection of a right.\n\nNecessity of data processing for legitimate interests of the data controller without harming fundamental rights and freedoms of the Relevant Person:\nPersonal data can be processed provided that the balance of interests of the Relevant Person is observed. In this context, primarily the legitimate interest that Smile Hair Clinic will obtain as a result of the processing activity is determined in processing data based on legitimate interest. The possible effect of processing personal data on the rights and freedoms of the Relevant Person is evaluated and if it is concluded that the balance is not disturbed, processing activity can be performed without seeking Explicit Consent.',
    'section2C': 'C. Conditions for Processing Special Category Personal Data',
    'section2CContent': 'Special category personal data is specified in a limited number in Article 6 of KVKK. These are; data regarding race, ethnic origin, political opinion, philosophical belief, religion, sect or other beliefs, appearance and clothing, membership to associations, foundations or trade unions, health, sexual life, criminal conviction and security measures, as well as biometric and genetic data.\n\nSmile Hair Clinic can process special category personal data in the following cases by ensuring that additional measures determined by the Board are taken:\n\nProcessing of special category personal data other than health and sexual life:\nIt can be processed without seeking the Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person if the relevant person gives Explicit Consent or if it is explicitly provided for in laws.\n\nPersonal data regarding health and sexual life:\nIt can be processed without seeking the Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person if the Relevant Person gives Explicit Consent or if it is processed by persons under the obligation of keeping secrets or authorized institutions and organizations for the purposes of protecting public health, preventive medicine, medical diagnosis, treatment and care services, planning and management of health services and their financing. Regardless of which processing reason it depends on, general data processing principles are always taken into account in processing processes and compliance with these principles is ensured. Regarding the protection of special category data, "Special Category Personal Data Protection Policy" has been put into effect in our company and actions are taken in accordance with the provisions of this policy in our business units and necessary measures are taken.\n\nHowever, processing of special category personal data is possible provided that at least one of the following cases specified in GDPR Article 9 exists. In case of existence of these situations, special category personal data can be processed by ensuring the appropriate security level also foreseen under KVKK:\n\n• In case the relevant person has explicit consent\n• For the data controller to fulfill its obligations under the Labor Law and Social Security Law\n• In case the relevant person is unable to give consent physically or legally\n• In case data is disclosed to the public by the relevant person\n• In case legal claims are made and data processing is necessary within the relevant judicial framework\n• Processing data for public interest provided that necessary technical and administrative measures are taken\n• For preventive medicine or occupational medicine purposes\n• For public interest archive and research activities pursuant to GDPR Article 89/1 based on EU Law.',
    
    // Section 3
    'section3': 'III. PERSONAL DATA CATEGORIES PROCESSED BY SMILE HAIR CLINIC',
    'section3Content': 'Personal data of the Relevant Person is processed by Smile Hair Clinic in the following categories in accordance with KVKK, GDPR and relevant other legislation provisions, within the framework of the purposes and conditions specified in this Policy:\n\nIdentity Information:\nInformation clearly belonging to a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable; processed partially or completely automatically or non-automatically as part of a data recording system; information contained in documents such as Driver\'s License, Identity Card, Residence, Passport, Marriage Certificate.\n\nContact Information:\nInformation clearly belonging to a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable; processed partially or completely automatically or non-automatically as part of a data recording system; information such as phone number, address, e-mail.\n\nPersonnel Information:\nInformation clearly belonging to a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable, processed partially or completely automatically or non-automatically as part of a data recording system; all kinds of personal data processed for the purpose of obtaining information that will form the basis for the personnel rights of our employees or real persons in a working relationship with Smile Hair Clinic.\n\nLegal Transaction Information:\nInformation clearly belonging to a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable, processed partially or completely automatically or non-automatically as part of a data recording system; your personal data processed within the scope of determination and follow-up of our legal receivables and rights, fulfillment of our debts, our legal obligations and compliance with Smile Hair Clinic policies.\n\nCustomer Transaction Information:\nInformation clearly belonging to and included in the data recording system of a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable; information such as records for the use of our products and services and instructions and requests necessary for the customer to use products and services.\n\nPhysical Space Security Information:\nPersonal data clearly belonging to and included in the data recording system of a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable; personal data regarding records and documents taken upon entry to physical space and during stay in the physical space.\n\nTransaction Security Information:\nPersonal data clearly belonging to and included in the data recording system of a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable; personal data processed to ensure technical, administrative, legal and commercial security while activities are carried out.\n\nFinance:\nPersonal data clearly belonging to a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable, processed partially or completely automatically or non-automatically as part of a data recording system; processed personal data regarding information, documents and records showing all kinds of financial results created according to the type of legal relationship established by Smile Hair Clinic with the relevant person.\n\nProfessional Experience:\nPersonal data clearly belonging to a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable, processed partially or completely automatically or non-automatically as part of a data recording system; personal data processed for the purpose of measuring the performance of our employees or real persons in a working relationship with our Company and planning and carrying out their career development within the scope of Smile Hair Clinic human resources policy.\n\nMarketing Information:\nPersonal data clearly belonging to a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable, processed partially or completely automatically or non-automatically as part of a data recording system; personal data processed for the purpose of marketing our products and services customized according to the usage habits, preferences and needs of the relevant person, and reports and evaluations created as a result of this processing.\n\nVisual and Audio Records:\nPersonal data clearly belonging to a natural person whose identity is certain or determinable; processed partially or completely automatically or non-automatically as part of a data recording system; Example: data contained in documents that are copies of documents containing personal data, such as photographs and camera records (except records within the scope of Physical Space Security Information), audio records.\n\nSpecial Category Personal Data:\nData regarding health and sexual life, data regarding criminal conviction and security measures.',
    
    // Section 4
    'section4': 'IV. TRANSFER OF PERSONAL DATA',
    'section4A': 'A. Transfer of Personal Data',
    'section4AContent': 'Data transfer is carried out for purposes such as ensuring the fulfillment of Smile Hair Clinic\'s activity and establishment purposes, ensuring that services necessary for Smile Hair Clinic to carry out its commercial activities, which it obtains from suppliers as external sources, are provided to our Company, ensuring the execution of human resources and employment policies, ensuring the fulfillment of obligations and taking necessary measures within the framework of occupational health and safety, and providing necessary information to authorized public institutions and organizations.\n\nBy Smile Hair Clinic, personal data belonging to relevant persons is not transferred to other persons without the explicit consent of the relevant person, except for cases where transfer of personal data to administrative and judicial institutions and organizations is mandatory under KVKK, GDPR or relevant legislation.\n\nHowever, personal data and special category personal data of the Relevant Person can be transferred to natural persons and private law legal entities, shareholders, suppliers and authorized public institutions and organizations and other relevant parties without seeking explicit consent by taking necessary security measures in line with personal data processing purposes in cases where there is a reason for compliance with law. In this direction, actions are taken in accordance with the regulations foreseen in Article 8 of KVKK and/or Articles 6 and 8 and Part 5 of GDPR.\n\nWithin the scope of KVKK, personal data can be transferred to third parties by Smile Hair Clinic with due care and by taking all necessary security measures, including the methods foreseen by the KVK Board, even if the Relevant Person does not have Explicit Consent, provided that one or more of the conditions specified below exist:\n\n• Explicit provision of relevant activities regarding transfer of personal data in laws\n• Necessity for protecting the life or physical integrity of the person who is unable to express consent due to actual impossibility or whose consent is not recognized as legally valid, or another person\n• Direct relation and necessity of transfer of personal data with establishment or performance of a contract\n• Necessity of transfer of personal data for fulfillment of a legal obligation\n• Limited transfer for the purpose of disclosure, provided that personal data is disclosed by the Relevant Person\n• Necessity of transfer of personal data for establishment, exercise or protection of rights of Smile Hair Clinic or the relevant person or third parties\n• Necessity of carrying out personal data transfer activity for legitimate interests of Smile Hair Clinic without harming fundamental rights and freedoms of the Relevant Person\n\nIn addition to the above, personal data can be transferred to foreign countries declared by the KVK Board to have adequate protection if any of the above conditions exist. In case adequate protection is not found, personal data can be transferred to foreign countries where data controllers in Turkey and the relevant foreign country commit in writing to provide adequate protection and where the KVK Board has permission, without the Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person.\n\nWithin the scope of GDPR; circulation of personal data within the European Union is free in accordance with Articles 6 and 8 of GDPR. Transfer outside the European Union is possible as regulated in Part 5 where Articles 44 and 50 are located. According to GDPR Article 44, appropriate security level must be ensured for a transfer outside the European Union. According to GDPR Article 45, a decision by the European Union Commission is required that the relevant country, region or relevant sector in that place has adequate security level. However, according to Article 46, transfer of personal data to the relevant third country is possible by the data controller, provided that effective legal remedies are available for relevant persons.',
    'section4B': 'B. Transfer of Special Category Personal Data',
    'section4BContent': 'Special category personal data can be transferred by Smile Hair Clinic in accordance with the principles specified in this Policy and by taking all necessary technical and administrative measures, including the methods to be determined by the Board, and provided that the following conditions exist.\n\nSpecial category personal data other than health and sexual life can be processed without seeking the Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person if it is explicitly provided for in laws, in other words, if there is an explicit provision in the relevant law regarding processing of personal data. Otherwise, the Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person will be obtained.\n\nSpecial category personal data regarding health and sexual life can be processed without seeking explicit consent if it is processed by persons under the obligation of keeping secrets or authorized institutions and organizations for the purposes of protecting public health, preventive medicine, medical diagnosis, treatment and care services, planning and management of health services and their financing. Otherwise, the Explicit Consent of the Relevant Person will be obtained.\n\nIn addition to the above, personal data can be transferred to foreign countries with adequate protection if any of the above conditions exist. In case adequate protection is not found, it can be transferred to foreign countries where Data Controller / Data Processor committing to provide adequate protection is located, in accordance with data transfer conditions foreseen in the legislation.\n\nRegarding transfer of special category personal data, "Special Category Personal Data Protection Policy" has been put into effect in our company and actions are taken in accordance with the provisions of this policy in our studies and necessary measures are taken. Regardless of which processing reason it depends on, general data processing principles are always taken into account in transfer processes and compliance with these principles is ensured.',
    
    // Section 5
    'section5': 'V. MATTERS REGARDING PROTECTION OF PERSONAL DATA',
    'section5Content': 'Smile Hair Clinic, in accordance with Article 12 of KVKK and Article 32 of GDPR, takes necessary technical and administrative measures to ensure appropriate security level to prevent unlawful processing of personal data it processes and unlawful access to data, and to ensure preservation of data, and conducts or has conducted necessary audits in this context.\n\nSystems compatible with technological developments are used for protection of personal data in secure environments. Technical security systems are installed for storage areas, technical measures taken are audited periodically by the audit mechanism determined by Smile Hair Clinic, and necessary technological solutions are produced by re-evaluating matters that pose risks.\n\nIn contracts concluded by Smile Hair Clinic with relevant companies regarding storage of personal data; provisions are included regarding the persons to whom personal data is transferred taking necessary security measures for protection of personal data and ensuring compliance with these measures in their own organizations, and actions are taken in accordance with the provisions of Smile Hair Clinic\'s Personal Data Protection Procedure in Third Party Relations on this matter.\n\nThe data protection principles adopted by Smile Hair Clinic include the following:\n\n• Providing clear information to individuals about who uses their personal data and how\n• Processing personal data in the minimum scale necessary for these purposes, without causing harm to fundamental rights and freedoms of individuals, and not processing excessive data\n• Respecting the rights of the Relevant Person regarding their personal data, including the right of access\n• Keeping inventory of processed personal data categories\n• Keeping personal data accurate and up-to-date when necessary\n• Processing personal data in accordance with fairness and law\n• Processing personal data only when clearly necessary for legitimate corporate purposes\n• Storing personal data only for the periods required by legal regulations, legal obligations of Smile Hair Clinic or legitimate corporate interests and specified in Smile Hair Clinic Personal Data Retention and Disposal Policy\n• Transferring personal data abroad in accordance with the principles determined by KVKK and GDPR\n• Determining a Committee with special authority and responsibility regarding the personal data protection system\n• Application of exceptions permitted under legislation\n• Preparation of this Policy\n• Taking necessary technical and administrative measures determined by KVKK, GDPR and secondary legislation and the Board to ensure appropriate security level for all personal data\n• Processing only relevant and appropriate personal data',
    'section5A': 'A. Training Activities',
    'section5AContent': 'Smile Hair Clinic provides necessary training to employees within the scope of Policies and KVKK & GDPR Regulations and Procedures regarding protection of Personal Data. Training especially includes definitions and protection practices for Special Category Personal Data. If a Smile Hair Clinic employee accesses Personal Data physically or in computer environment, our Company provides training to the relevant employee specifically for these accesses (for example, the computer program accessed).\n\nSmile Hair Clinic ensures that employees are provided with training and necessary notifications are made to increase awareness to prevent unlawful processing of personal data, unlawful access to data and to ensure preservation of data.',
    'section5B': 'B. Audit Activities',
    'section5BContent': 'Smile Hair Clinic has the right to audit at any time and ex officio, without giving any prior notice, that all employees, departments and suppliers of the Company act in accordance with this Policy and KVKK&GDPR Regulations, and conducts or has conducted necessary routine audits in this context. These audit results are evaluated within the scope of the Company\'s internal operations and necessary activities are carried out to improve the measures taken.',
    
    // Section 6
    'section6': 'VI. RETENTION AND DISPOSAL OF PERSONAL DATA',
    'section6Content': 'Smile Hair Clinic retains personal data in accordance with the period necessary for the purpose for which they are processed and the minimum periods foreseen in the legislation to which the relevant activity is subject. In this context, first it is determined whether a period is foreseen in the relevant legislation for retention of personal data, and if a period is determined, behavior is in accordance with this period. If no period exists in the legislation, personal data is retained for the period necessary for the purpose for which they are processed. Personal data is disposed of at the end of the determined retention periods in accordance with the periodic disposal periods determined in Smile Hair Clinic Personal Data Retention and Disposal Policy or the application of the Relevant Person, and using the determined disposal methods (deletion and/or destruction and/or anonymization).\n\nFor detailed information, you can access Smile Hair Clinic Personal Data Retention and Disposal Policy at www.smilehairclinic.com.',
    
    // Section 7
    'section7': 'VII. INFORMING AND NOTIFICATION OF THE RELEVANT PERSON',
    'section7Content': 'Smile Hair Clinic informs the Relevant Person in accordance with KVKK, GDPR and secondary regulations. In this context, personal data is explained to the Relevant Person at the time of acquisition if obtained from the Relevant Person themselves; within a reasonable period from the acquisition of personal data if not obtained from the Relevant Person; but in any case, regardless of the request of the Relevant Person:\n\n• Identity of Smile Hair Clinic\n• For what purpose personal data will be processed\n• To whom and for what purposes it can be transferred\n• Method of personal data collection (which of completely or partially automatic methods or which of non-automatic methods as part of a data recording system is used)\n• What legal reason personal data collection is based on\n• Other rights of the Relevant Person specified in KVKK or GDPR\n\nare explained.\n\nThe informing in question must definitely include the rights of the Relevant Person specified in KVKK, GDPR and this Policy, in addition to the above. The following matters are taken into account when informing:\n\n• Information within the scope of informing is carried out using clear and simple language. Expressions that give the impression that relevant personal data may be processed for other purposes that may come to the agenda in the future are not used.\n• Informing can be done through various physical or electronic channels through call center verbally, in writing, through voice recording, and redirecting can be made to the web page where personal data informing texts are located and other channels that can be announced later. The relevant section that provides information and fulfills the obligation of informing takes measures to prove this in accordance with law and procedure.\n• If the data processing purpose specified in the informing changes while a personal data is being obtained, the obligation of informing for this new purpose is also fulfilled in accordance with the procedures foreseen above.\n• If the obtained personal data will only be used for the purpose of establishing communication with the Relevant Person, informing can be done at the time of establishing the first communication.\n• Attention is paid to ensuring that informing is carried out at the latest when personal data will be transferred to third parties for the first time if the obtained personal data will be transferred to third parties.',
    
    // Section 8
    'section8': 'VIII. RIGHTS OF THE RELEVANT PERSON AND EXERCISE OF THESE RIGHTS',
    'section8Content': 'Legal rights that the Relevant Person can use regarding personal data are listed below:\n\n• Learning whether personal data is processed\n• Requesting information if personal data is processed\n• Learning the purpose of processing personal data and whether they are used in accordance with their purpose\n• Learning third parties to whom personal data is transferred domestically or abroad\n• Requesting correction if personal data is processed incompletely or inaccurately and requesting notification of the transaction made in this context to third parties to whom personal data is transferred\n• Requesting deletion, destruction or anonymization of personal data and notification of the transaction made in this context to third parties to whom personal data is transferred if reasons requiring processing are eliminated despite processing in accordance with law and relevant other law provisions\n• Objecting to a result arising against the person by analyzing the processed data exclusively through automatic systems\n• Requesting compensation for damage if damage is suffered due to unlawful processing of personal data\n• Requesting transfer of personal data to a different data controller requested by the relevant person (right to data portability)\n\nThe Relevant Person, if a Turkey resident, can submit their requests regarding the rights specified in this article to Smile Hair Clinic by filling out the Smile Hair Clinic Application Form in writing in Turkish in accordance with the Notification on Procedures and Principles for Application to Data Controller numbered 30356, or if a European resident, in English, or by using Registered Electronic Mail (KEP) address, Secure Electronic Signature, Mobile Signature or the electronic mail address previously notified and registered in our system.',
    'section9': 'IX. RESPONSE OF SMILE HAIR CLINIC TO APPLICATIONS',
    'section9Content': 'Smile Hair Clinic takes all necessary technical and administrative measures to conclude applications to be made by the Relevant Person effectively, in accordance with law and rules of integrity.\n\nApplications of the Relevant Person can be accepted or rejected with justification. Response to the application of the Relevant Person can be notified to the Relevant Person in writing or in electronic environment.\n\nIf the Relevant Person submits their request regarding the rights under the heading numbered VIII titled "Rights of the Relevant Person and Exercise of These Rights" in the Policy to Smile Hair Clinic in accordance with the mentioned procedures, the relevant request will be concluded free of charge as soon as possible and within 30 (thirty) days at the latest, depending on the nature of the request. However, if the transaction requires an additional cost and conditions determined by the KVK Board are met, the fee in the tariff can be requested.',
    
    // Section 10
    'section10': 'X. EFFECTIVENESS AND UPDATE PERIOD OF THE POLICY',
    'section10Content': 'This Policy prepared by Smile Hair Clinic entered into force on 01.05.2021, and necessary updates will be made in case of renewal of all or certain articles of the Policy.\n\nThe Committee executes the implementation, update and announcement of this Policy. The Policy is published on the Smile Hair Clinic website.\n\nLast Update: July 24, 2025',
    
    // Footer
    'footerCompany': 'Smile Hair Health Services and Tourism Consultancy Ltd. Co.',
    'footerEmail': 'Email: info@smilehairclinic.com',
    'footerAddress': 'Address: Tatlısu, Alptekin Cd. No:15, 34774 Ümraniye/Istanbul, Turkey',
    'footerPhone': 'Phone: +90 549 149 24 00',
    'footerCopyright': '© Copyright 2025 Smile Hair Clinic. All Rights Reserved',
  };
  
